## 6. Standard Response Envelopes

## 6.1 Success Envelope

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {},
  "meta": {
    "request_id": "req_01HZX9YV",
    "timestamp": "2026-06-22T10:30:00Z",
    "api_version": "v1"
  }
}
```

## 6.2 List Envelope

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": [
    {}
  ],
  "pagination": {
    "page": 1,
    "page_size": 20,
    "total_count": 126,
    "total_pages": 7,
    "has_next": true,
    "has_previous": false
  },
  "meta": {
    "request_id": "req_01HZX9YV",
    "timestamp": "2026-06-22T10:30:00Z"
  }
}
```

## 6.3 Action Response Envelope

Workflow action endpoints should return:

```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "entity_type": "loan_application",
    "entity_id": "uuid",
    "previous_status": "appraisal_reviewed",
    "new_status": "submitted_to_sanction_committee",
    "workflow_event_id": "uuid",
    "available_actions": []
  },
  "meta": {
    "request_id": "req_01HZX9YV",
    "timestamp": "2026-06-22T10:30:00Z"
  }
}
```

